        Note that this name can be different from the name specified on the name. See CellPathResolver.getCanonicalCellName(java.nio.file.Path) for more information.

        Specified by:

      • getCellPath

        public Path getCellPath()
        Description copied from interface: UnconfiguredBuildTarget
        The path to the root of the cell where this build target is used.

        Note that the same build target name can reference different build targets when used in different cells. For example, given a target name external_cell//lib:target, for a cell that maps external_cell to a cell with location /cells/cell_a, this build target would point to a target //lib:target in the /cells/cell_a cell (defined in a build file located in /cells/cell_a/lib folder. If another cell uses the same build target name, but points external_cell to a different cell, say /cells/cell_b, then this build target refers to a target //lib:target in the /cells/cell_b cell.

        Specified by:
        getCellPath in interface UnconfiguredBuildTarget
